"Transfer sticky dough to a very well floured surface and divide into 4 pieces. Carefully, using floured hands, shape each piece into an oval (approx. 18 cm long), being careful not to remove too much air from dough. Place on prepared baking tray, cover then set aside to rest for a further 30 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 200°C."},{"content":"Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid, weigh in 80 g water and 10 g bread flour, add bicarbonate of soda and mix using a fork."},{"content":"Brush loaves with the soda-flour glaze, dip spatula in soda-flour glaze and then use to form 4 lengthwise indents. Sprinkle two loaves with sesame seeds and two with poppy seeds then bake for 25-30 minutes (200°C). Set aside to cool for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Herbs and Walnut Dip"},{"content":"Place walnuts in mixing bowl and toast <b>4 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add basil, tarragon, mint, coriander and chives then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add feta cheese and olive oil then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Serve flatbreads with the dip."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Try sprinkling with fennel seeds for a different flavour."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h 35m","4 portions"]}